ğ—›ğ—¼ğ˜„ ğ—¶ğ˜ ğ˜„ğ—¼ğ—¿ğ—¸ğ˜€: Kubernetes opens a static port (usually in the 30000-32767 range) on the IP address of every Node in your cluster.

ğ—ªğ—µğ˜† ğ˜‚ğ˜€ğ—² ğ—¶ğ˜: External traffic reaches your application by hitting <NodeIP>:<NodePort>, which is then routed by Kubernetes to your Service and its Pods. It's a straightforward way to get traffic into the cluster.

